  "body": "# Issue\r\n\r\nI use contracts from an npm package. When running tests without migrations I use this trick to make npm contracts code appear in build/contracts and deploy them using `artifacts.require`. \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ensdomains/resolvers/blob/master/test/mocks/dummy.sol\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Import an npm package with a smart contract\r\n    ```\r\n    truffle init\r\n    npm i @ensdomains/ens\r\n    ```\r\n2. Add `artifacts.require('@ensdomains/ens/ENSRegistry')` in a new test\r\n3. `truffle test`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nWork! Find the npm contract in build, without adding that patch\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macos, ubuntu (in circleci)\r\n* Ethereum client: truffle develop\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): latest\r\n* node version (`node --version`): latest\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): latest\r\n",
